keyFacts: Travel authorization 10982117 was approved on January 29, 2020 for witness interviews related to investigation 2018R01618.
The travel was scheduled from February 3-8, 2020, indicating ongoing investigative activity in early 2020.
The traveler's name is redacted in the document, but the purpose is clearly stated as witness interviews.
The document originates from the DOJ's E2 travel system, showing bureaucratic processes within the investigation.
The authorization status was 'Pending Authorization Approval' despite being 'approved by' someone, indicating multi-level approval requirements.
